task.summary: Default task
- Refactoring and Cleanup
- Updated Copyright and Permissions
- Bluetooth Classic Scanning Implemented... Bluetooth LE will follow, then iBeacon, than I'll build the UI to take and record measurements
- Bluetooth LE scanning is now supported (Part 1)
- Bluetooth LE scanning is now supported (Part 2)
- Bluetooth LE scanning is now supported (Part 2)
- A lot of refactoring and better code cohesion between the Bluetooth and Bluetooth LE Collector implementations

- Bluetooth LE Collector now supports both the old Bluetooth LE Android API first introduced on Android 4.3 Lollipop (aka API Level 18) and the newer (much better) API that was added on Android 5.0 Lollipop (aka API Level 23). It detects which version of Android you are running and chooses the best implementation accordingly. However, I still need to test on older devices to make sure it really works gracefully.
- Project updated to the latest Android development tools (i.e., Android Studio 2.0, etc.)
- Nothing worth noting
- Beacon Scanning implemented using the AltBeacon library
- Some improvements
- Whatever
- Playing with CSV logs... However, I'm considering dumping them in favor of something more fancy...!
- Improved logging but still unfinished
- Refactoring - Minor fixes - I still haven't tested if I have fixed the JsonLogger bug
- JsonLogger Bug fix
- JsonLogger Bug fix
- Basic logging working - More improvements needed
- Improvements, bugfixes and some refactoring
